== English ==
=== Etymology 1 ===
From [[w:Spanish language|Spanish]] [[Diego]], a common Spanish name.  See [[Johnnie]] and [[Jock]] for similar epithets.
==== Noun ====
[[Category:English nouns]]
[[Category:English slang]]
# (''Commonwealth English, slang'') A [[person]] of [[w:Hispanic|Spanish]] or [[w:Portuguese people|Portuguese]] [[descent]].
#:'''Usage notes:''' The [[sense]] has become less [[pejorative]] in recent years, with people of Spanish or Portuguese origin themselves adopting the term.
